8. Victim  and  witness  protection.(1)  In  addition  to  the  existing laws, a victim and witness protection system may be established as prescribed in the rules notified by the ministry of law and justice and shall, with a view to carrying out the purposes of this Act and without generality of the aforesaid, include the following, namely: -
6. (i) special security arrangements for witnesses and victims;
7. (ii) concealment of identity;
8. (iii) distance  recording  of  testimonies  through  video-conferencing,  audiovideo links and by the use of modem devices;
9. (iv) re-location of victims and witnesses;
10. (v) provision of reasonable financial assistance;
11. (vi) compensation to legal heirs of protected victims and witnesses;
12. (vii) safe-houses, dar-ul-amans, etc.;
13. (viii) such other measures as may be necessary and ancillary.
(2) Till  such  time  the  rules  envisaged  in  sub-section  (1)  are  prescribed, provincial or ICT witness protection laws as the case may be, shall be applicable to both victims and witnesses under this Act mutatis mutandis.

