2. (a) case number;
3. (b) item number;
4. (c) description; and
5. (d) date of recovery or receiving.
8. Chain  of  Custody. -(1)  The  investigation  officer  and  all  other persons under the Act and rules involved in the process of collection, transmission, examination or otherwise of the evidence in any way shall maintain a safe chain of custody for the evidence.
